~ This file last changed in version 4.21.0 ~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

DEPENDENCIES
============
- Gtk2 styling requires the Gtk2 'murrine' engine package, installation instructions below
- Gtk styling of Qt5.7+ requires the 'Qt5 style plugins' package, installation instructions below

System tuning
-------------
- Qt5.x apps require the environment variable QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME to be set to gtk2, setup instructions below
- Qt5.x apps, at least up to Qt5.10, may produce slightly fuzzy fonts on some Xfce systems (see https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-56809); the lines containing '#xfce-evolution' in the install/uninstall instructions below will apply/undo a fix for this issue which will work on most modern Xfce systems (spcecifically, on systems which use a typical CRT or LCD screen and which use the default Xfce font highlighting 'slight')

Recommends
----------
The Xfce desktop just isn't complete without the Nemo file manager (optional install).
The Xfce Evolution theme blends well with Google's 'Noto' fonts (optional install) and the 'elementary Xfce darker' icon set (optional install).


INSTALLATION
============
THE INSTALLATION PROCEDURE DESCRIBED BELOW MAY CHANGE FOR EACH NEW VERSION, whereby requirements and/or install steps may be added/changed/removed. Any such changes are documented in the 'HISTORY' file inside the installer package for each new release.

IMPORTANT
---------
The installation procedure below will install 'Xfce Evolution' FOR YOUR OWN USER from the 'xfce-evolution-n.n.n.zip' archive. Your distribution may also provide an 'Xfce Evolution' package/port, which will install 'Xfce Evolution' for all users.

The install procedure for your own user consists of the following 3 steps:

1) Remove your existing 'Xfce Evolution' files from your themes folder, if any:
   rm -R -f ~/.themes/'Xfce Evolution'*
2) Extract AT LEAST the 'Xfce Evolution' base theme folder from the 'xfce-evolution-n.n.n.zip' archive into your themes folder '~/.themes/'
  - IMPORTANT: you must use a modern version of 'unzip' which PROPERLY EXTRACTS SYMLINKS
3) Install/update 'Xfce Evolution'-specific system tuning (including dependencies):
  - run the install helper '~/.themes/Xfce Evolution/TOOLS/SETUP/install_helper.sh', OR
  - if the install helper does not provide an option for your distribution, or if you do not wish to run the install script, then see 'Manually install system-tuning' paragraph below

Manually install system-tuning
------------------------------
To "manually" install/update the 'Xfce evolution'-specific system tuning (including dependencies), REPLACE step (3) above with the following:

  3a) Install/update the 'gtk2 murrine engine' and 'qt5 style plusings' dependencies by using your package manager:
    - e.g. for Ubuntu use 'apt install gtk2-engines-murrine qt5-style-plugins'
  3b) set the QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME environment variable in ALL your shell initialization files (this setting is required for qt5+ to pick up the gtk2 theme), and mark this setting with '#xfce-evolution' hash-tag such that it can be easily identified and removed on uninstall:
    -e.g. for bash shells you will have to add a line 'export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=gtk2 #xfce-evolution' in all the bash initialiation files which exist in your home directory: '~/.bash_profile', '~/.bash_login', and '~/.profile'
  3c) apply the qt5 font fix patch:
      mkdir -p ~/.config/fontconfig/conf.d
      cp ~/.themes/'Xfce Evolution'/90-xfce-evolution_qt5fontfix.conf ~/.config/fontconfig/conf.d/

Sub-themes
----------
The Xfce Evolution theme contains multiple "sub-themes", each stored in a separate folder after installation (e.g. the 'Xfce Evolution Bronze' folder for the Xfce Evolution Bronze sub-theme, etc). You may safely remove any sub-theme folders which you do not (intend to) use, EXCEPT THE MAIN THEME 'Xfce Evolution' folder. The 'Xfce Evolution' folder contains COMMON DATA REQUIRED BY ALL SUB-THEMES, such that deleting this folder will render all sub-themes unusable.

Display settings
----------------
The 'Xfce Evolution' theme contains a collection of "display themes" (Xfce Settings Panel -> Appearance -> Themes), plus a "window manager theme" (Xfce Settings Panel -> Appearance -> Window Manager); in this context:
- the 'Xfce Evolution' display themes blend well with 'Noto Sans 9'/'DejaVu Sans Book 9'/'Bitstream Vera Sans 9' fonts and 'elementary Xfce darkER' icon set, and they scale consistently across gtk2/gtk3 applications for font sizes [7-11]@96dpi
- for a consistent look of window decorations across xfwm and gtk3-csd windows you should select the 'Xfce Evolution' window manager theme when using the 'Xfce Evolution' display themes
- for a consistent look of the window titles across xfwm and gtk3-csd windows you should select the same font family (with style 'regular') and the same font size for the window manager titles as you selected for your display theme


UNINSTALL
=========
The uninstall procedure below removes 'Xfce Evolution' FOR YOUR OWN USER, and it applies ONLY if you installed 'Xfce Evolution' from the 'xfce-evolution-n.n.n.zip' archive according to the installation instructions described in the 'INSTALLATION' chapter in this document. If you installed 'Xfce Evolution' by using your package manager (e.g. from your distribution's repository) then you MUST use your package manager to uninstall it.

The uninstall procedure for your own user consists of the following 2 steps:

1) Remove the 'Xfce Evolution'-specific system tuning (dependencies will not be removed):
  - run the uninstall helper '~/.themes/Xfce Evolution/TOOLS/SETUP/uninstall_helper.sh', OR
  - if the uninstall helper does not provide an option for your distribution, or if you do not wish to run the uninstall script, then see 'Manually remove system-tuning' paragraph below
2) delete all the Xfce Evolution theme's folders form within your '~/.themes' folder:
   rm -R -f ~/.themes/'Xfce Evolution'*

Manually remove system-tuning
-----------------------------
To "manually" remove the 'Xfce evolution'-specific system tuning (excluding the dependencies), REPLACE step (1) above with the following:

  1a) remove the qt5 font fix patch:
      rm -f ~/.config/fontconfig/conf.d/90-xfce-evolution_qt5fontfix.conf
  2b) remove all the lines which contain the '#xfce-evolution' hash-tag from ALL the shell initialization files which are present in your home directory (this will remove only the QT_QPA_PLATFORMTEME setting in the current version):
    - e.g. for csh/tcsh shells: sed -i.bak '/#xfce-evolution/d' '~/.tcshrc' '~/.cshrc'


CUSTOMIZATION
=============
The 'Xfce Evolution' theme supports several end-user tweaking options, see 'Xfce Evolution/TOOLS/CONFIG/HACKING' inside the 'xfce-evolution-n.n.n.zip' archive for details.
